            <description><![CDATA[üöÄ From Zero to GitOps: Spinning Up the Infrahub + Vidra Demo in Codespaces]]></description>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id="-from-zero-to-gitops-spinning-up-the-infrahub--vidra-demo-in-codespaces">üöÄ From Zero to GitOps: Spinning Up the Infrahub + Vidra Demo in Codespaces<a href="https://infrahub-operator.github.io/vidra/blog/demo#-from-zero-to-gitops-spinning-up-the-infrahub--vidra-demo-in-codespaces" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to üöÄ From Zero to GitOps: Spinning Up the Infrahub + Vidra Demo in Codespaces" title="Direct link to üöÄ From Zero to GitOps: Spinning Up the Infrahub + Vidra Demo in Codespaces">‚Äã</a></h2>
<p>Are you curious about how modern infrastructure modeling meets hands-off Kubernetes deployment? The <a href="https://github.com/infrahub-operator/infrahub-vidra-demo" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">infrahub-vidra-demo</a> is your playground! In this post, we‚Äôll walk through how you can launch a complete, production-like GitOps environment‚Äîright in your browser, with no local setup‚Äîusing GitHub Codespaces.</p>
<h3 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id="why-this-demo">Why This Demo?<a href="https://infrahub-operator.github.io/vidra/blog/demo#why-this-demo" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Why This Demo?" title="Direct link to Why This Demo?">‚Äã</a></h3>
<p>Traditional GitOps workflows often require you to handcraft YAML files and wire up complex pipelines. With Infrahub and Vidra, you get a streamlined, user-friendly approach: model your infrastructure visually, let Vidra handle the deployment, and enjoy full traceability‚Äîall in a few clicks.</p>
<h3 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id="step-1-launch-codespaces-and-initialize">Step 1: Launch Codespaces and Initialize<a href="https://infrahub-operator.github.io/vidra/blog/demo#step-1-launch-codespaces-and-initialize" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Step 1: Launch Codespaces and Initialize" title="Direct link to Step 1: Launch Codespaces and Initialize">‚Äã</a></h3>
<p>Start by opening the <a href="https://github.com/infrahub-operator/infrahub-vidra-demo" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">demo repository</a>  in GitHub Codespaces. Just hit the green ‚ÄúCode‚Äù button and select ‚ÄúOpen with Codespaces‚Äù. Once your environment is ready, initialize everything with:</p>
<div class="language-bash codeBlockContainer_Ckt0 theme-code-block" style="--prism-color:#393A34;--prism-background-color:#f6f8fa"><div class="codeBlockContent_QJqH"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-bash codeBlock_bY9V thin-scrollbar" style="color:#393A34;background-color:#f6f8fa"><code class="codeBlockLines_e6Vv"><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">task init</span><br></span></code></pre></div></div>
<p>This single command spins up a local <a href="https://kind.sigs.k8s.io/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">kind</a> Kubernetes cluster and installs Infrahub, Vidra Operator, Vidra CLI, and a self-service frontend. No Docker, no Kubernetes setup‚Äîjust code.</p>
<p>Verify that Vidra Operator is running:</p>
<div class="language-bash codeBlockContainer_Ckt0 theme-code-block" style="--prism-color:#393A34;--prism-background-color:#f6f8fa"><div class="codeBlockContent_QJqH"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-bash codeBlock_bY9V thin-scrollbar" style="color:#393A34;background-color:#f6f8fa"><code class="codeBlockLines_e6Vv"><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">kubectl get pod -n vidra-system</span><br></span></code></pre></div></div>
<div class="theme-admonition theme-admonition-note admonition_xJq3 alert alert--secondary"><div class="admonitionHeading_Gvgb"><span class="admonitionIcon_Rf37"><svg viewBox="0 0 14 16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M6.3 5.69a.942.942 0 0 1-.28-.7c0-.28.09-.52.28-.7.19-.18.42-.28.7-.28.28 0 .52.09.7.28.18.19.28.42.28.7 0 .28-.09.52-.28.7a1 1 0 0 1-.7.3c-.28 0-.52-.11-.7-.3zM8 7.99c-.02-.25-.11-.48-.31-.69-.2-.19-.42-.3-.69-.31H6c-.27.02-.48.13-.69.31-.2.2-.3.44-.31.69h1v3c.02.27.11.5.31.69.2.2.42.31.69.31h1c.27 0 .48-.11.69-.31.2-.19.3-.42.31-.69H8V7.98v.01zM7 2.3c-3.14 0-5.7 2.54-5.7 5.68 0 3.14 2.56 5.7 5.7 5.7s5.7-2.55 5.7-5.7c0-3.15-2.56-5.69-5.7-5.69v.01zM7 .98c3.86 0 7 3.14 7 7s-3.14 7-7 7-7-3.12-7-7 3.14-7 7-7z"></path></svg></span>note</div><div class="admonitionContent_BuS1"><blockquote>
<p>Heads up: Shell completion and the <code>k</code> alias might not work in Codespaces, so use the full <code>kubectl</code> command.</p>
</blockquote></div></div>
<h3 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id="step-2-explore-the-ui">Step 2: Explore the UI<a href="https://infrahub-operator.github.io/vidra/blog/demo#step-2-explore-the-ui" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Step 2: Explore the UI" title="Direct link to Step 2: Explore the UI">‚Äã</a></h3>
<ul>
<li>Open the <strong>Ports</strong> tab in Codespaces.</li>
<li>Click the globe icon for port <code>8000</code> (Infrahub) and <code>5001</code> (Frontend).</li>
<li>In the frontend, submit a webserver request like <code>test/test</code>. This action creates a proposed change in Infrahub.</li>
<li>Log in to Infrahub (<code>admin</code> / <code>infrahub</code>), review, and merge the proposed change. Artifacts are generated and ready for deployment.</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id="step-3-sync-with-vidra">Step 3: Sync with Vidra<a href="https://infrahub-operator.github.io/vidra/blog/demo#step-3-sync-with-vidra" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Step 3: Sync with Vidra" title="Direct link to Step 3: Sync with Vidra">‚Äã</a></h3>
<p>Bring your modeled infrastructure to life in the cluster:</p>
<div class="language-bash codeBlockContainer_Ckt0 theme-code-block" style="--prism-color:#393A34;--prism-background-color:#f6f8fa"><div class="codeBlockContent_QJqH"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-bash codeBlock_bY9V thin-scrollbar" style="color:#393A34;background-color:#f6f8fa"><code class="codeBlockLines_e6Vv"><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">host_ip=$(hostname -I | awk '{print $1}')</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">vidra-cli credentials apply https://${host_ip} --username admin --password infrahub</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">vidra-cli infrahubsync apply "http://${host_ip}:8000" -a Webserver_Manifest -b main -N default -e</span><br></span></code></pre></div></div>
<p>If you‚Äôre running locally (not in Codespaces), you can use:</p>
<div class="language-bash codeBlockContainer_Ckt0 theme-code-block" style="--prism-color:#393A34;--prism-background-color:#f6f8fa"><div class="codeBlockContent_QJqH"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-bash codeBlock_bY9V thin-scrollbar" style="color:#393A34;background-color:#f6f8fa"><code class="codeBlockLines_e6Vv"><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">task vidra-add-sync</span><br></span></code></pre></div></div>
<h3 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id="step-4-dive-deeper">Step 4: Dive Deeper<a href="https://infrahub-operator.github.io/vidra/blog/demo#step-4-dive-deeper" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Step 4: Dive Deeper" title="Direct link to Step 4: Dive Deeper">‚Äã</a></h3>
<p>Want to see what Vidra is managing? Try:</p>
<div class="language-bash codeBlockContainer_Ckt0 theme-code-block" style="--prism-color:#393A34;--prism-background-color:#f6f8fa"><div class="codeBlockContent_QJqH"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-bash codeBlock_bY9V thin-scrollbar" style="color:#393A34;background-color:#f6f8fa"><code class="codeBlockLines_e6Vv"><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">kubectl get infrahubsyncs.infrahub.operators.com -o yaml</span><br></span></code></pre></div></div>
<div class="language-bash codeBlockContainer_Ckt0 theme-code-block" style="--prism-color:#393A34;--prism-background-color:#f6f8fa"><div class="codeBlockContent_QJqH"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-bash codeBlock_bY9V thin-scrollbar" style="color:#393A34;background-color:#f6f8fa"><code class="codeBlockLines_e6Vv"><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">kubectl get vidraresources.infrahub.operators.com</span><br></span></code></pre></div></div>
<div class="language-bash codeBlockContainer_Ckt0 theme-code-block" style="--prism-color:#393A34;--prism-background-color:#f6f8fa"><div class="codeBlockContent_QJqH"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-bash codeBlock_bY9V thin-scrollbar" style="color:#393A34;background-color:#f6f8fa"><code class="codeBlockLines_e6Vv"><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">kubectl get vidraresources.infrahub.operators.com -o yaml</span><br></span></code></pre></div></div>
<div class="language-bash codeBlockContainer_Ckt0 theme-code-block" style="--prism-color:#393A34;--prism-background-color:#f6f8fa"><div class="codeBlockContent_QJqH"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-bash codeBlock_bY9V thin-scrollbar" style="color:#393A34;background-color:#f6f8fa"><code class="codeBlockLines_e6Vv"><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">kubectl get &lt;kind&gt; &lt;name&gt; -n &lt;namespace&gt;</span><br></span></code></pre></div></div>
<p>Or launch <a href="https://k9scli.io/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">k9s</a> for a terminal UI:</p>
<div class="language-bash codeBlockContainer_Ckt0 theme-code-block" style="--prism-color:#393A34;--prism-background-color:#f6f8fa"><div class="codeBlockContent_QJqH"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-bash codeBlock_bY9V thin-scrollbar" style="color:#393A34;background-color:#f6f8fa"><code class="codeBlockLines_e6Vv"><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">k9s</span><br></span></code></pre></div></div>
<h3 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id="step-5-forward-to-the-webserver">Step 5: Forward to the Webserver<a href="https://infrahub-operator.github.io/vidra/blog/demo#step-5-forward-to-the-webserver" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Step 5: Forward to the Webserver" title="Direct link to Step 5: Forward to the Webserver">‚Äã</a></h3>
<p>To access the deployed webserver, forward the service port:</p>
<div class="language-bash codeBlockContainer_Ckt0 theme-code-block" style="--prism-color:#393A34;--prism-background-color:#f6f8fa"><div class="codeBlockContent_QJqH"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-bash codeBlock_bY9V thin-scrollbar" style="color:#393A34;background-color:#f6f8fa"><code class="codeBlockLines_e6Vv"><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">kubectl port-forward svc/test 8080:80 -n test</span><br></span></code></pre></div></div>
<p>List all available tasks with:</p>
<div class="language-bash codeBlockContainer_Ckt0 theme-code-block" style="--prism-color:#393A34;--prism-background-color:#f6f8fa"><div class="codeBlockContent_QJqH"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-bash codeBlock_bY9V thin-scrollbar" style="color:#393A34;background-color:#f6f8fa"><code class="codeBlockLines_e6Vv"><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">task</span><br></span></code></pre></div></div>
<hr>
<h3 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id="final-thoughts">Final Thoughts<a href="https://infrahub-operator.github.io/vidra/blog/demo#final-thoughts" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Final Thoughts" title="Direct link to Final Thoughts">‚Äã</a></h3>
<p>This demo isn‚Äôt just a quickstart‚Äîit‚Äôs a glimpse into the future of infrastructure management. Model your systems in Infrahub, let Vidra automate the deployment, and manage everything through intuitive UIs. Whether you‚Äôre a platform engineer or just exploring GitOps, this Codespaces-powered demo is the fastest way to experience the workflow.</p>
<p><strong>Ready to try it? Jump in, experiment, and see how easy GitOps can be!</strong></p>]]></content:encoded>
